\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 That's right. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 It wasn't dished out to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Would the same be true of the mutton, did you help yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Oh no, that was - that was - that was - that was cut up by the old woman or the old man and - you got your own share.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Did you usually have just a spoon, or did you usually have a knife and a fork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Oh we had a spoon, but no we had knives and forks since I remembered anyway. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Everyday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Everyday. But we never had - knifes and fork with potatoes and herring. Use your fingers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 
Can you tell me whether you felt your mother or your father played the most important part in bringing you up in your ideas that they had about how to live or how to behave, or were they both the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Th
ey were both the same, they were just of the same interest, the woman, the old woman had a - a good suggestion about how to bring up well the old one wouldn't - interfere with it, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Can you tell me what they brought you up to consider important in l
ife, what in those days did they think important things in life were? Did they talk about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 
Oh yes. They - say if they saw a man, a young man coming home from the pub drink - oh - I never want to see you like that, now have a look at that man now, 
that's an example for you. Oh there would be a good lecture like that. Didn't want you to - they wanted you to be good, as good as - mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Did they talk to you quite a lot when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Did you ever tell them about things you were worried about or if you had nightmares at night, bad dreams and things, or didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Oh well, yes, you would if you had a headache or - something that - was - worried you, even a dream, you would tell them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 They were the sort of parents you could talk easily to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Sometimes people have told me in those days the parents were more distant from the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Do you think it wasn't like that here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Couldn't say anything about that, I don't really -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Did you have any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Oh plenty of books, yes. Yes, we used to have them to read and of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Was there a library going on then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Not - there was, oh yes, yes, yes, yes, yes, we used to go every - every Saturday
. Take the - take your old one back and you'd get another. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 What about newspapers and magazines did they have anything like that on the island?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Yes. Papers, yes. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 I know you have a lot of relations don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 But things like aunts and uncles and grandparents, did they live nearby, did they live in Bentangval?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 
Perhaps - perhaps you were living in Bentangval and your grandmother was at Norothbay. And you see, her daughters, they were married - this far from - from - Bentangval here, and - the grandmothers were at Northbay and - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Where were your own ones, your father had come from Mingulay hadn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Where were his parents when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 They were in Mingulay too. Yes. They died there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 The grandfather that used to jog you on his knee, was you're your mother's father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 He lived quite near?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Oh yes. Mm hm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 And granny, she was alive when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Mm. Oh she was alive when she - when I was born but I don't remember her. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Were relations in the house quite a lot and calling round, did you see a lot of them then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Yes. Oh yes, they were very good that way, they were - they were very clannish, they - we used to call on our own relations and - mm hm.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 What about neighbours and friends, did they come in often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Yes. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 If they came in would they be given a cup of tea or something or not usually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Oh yes, it - it was - a done thing in - 
in the - in the - in these olden times if your neighbour would come in just for a chat and you had - a cup of tea was going, well see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Did you hear like some people say in England some people are proud of keeping themselves to themselves, have you ev
er heard that expression?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3027436 PC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4155104 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10775577\charrsid1072312 Is that not something people value here, are people more open to neighbours do you think?
